history.text: Hello
Hi!
So, have you ever seen Jaws?
No, I havent! Is it any good?
If you are into horror movies, I guess you would enjoy it.
I do like horror movies. What makes it a scary movie?
It makes you want to stay away from the ocean.  It's about a shark that kills people.
Oh wow, that does sound scary. I do not like a lot of gore. Is it a very bloody movie?
Not really.  It's made in the 70s so it doesn't get as bloody as movies do now.
Oh i see! That sounds very interesting. Do you know where it takes place?
It's on a fictional island called Amity Island.  It's supposed to be located in the New England area.
That is very cool! Is it well made? or is it a B-Movie?
It did really well at the box office and is considered a classic horror movie.  I wouldn't consider it a B-Movie.  Plus, it was directed by Spielberg!
Oh wow, it must certainly be worth seeing then! What was it about Jaws that you liked the most?
I haven't seen from start to ending it myself, I just hear good things about it.  I always channel surf and watch bits and pieces.
I see. I often hear good things about it too but I never knew really what it was about or why it was so great.
I usually check Rotten Tomatoes for scores of movies.  This one has a 97% rate so it must be pretty good!
With such a high rating and an acclaimed director, im sure its great. I am just confused - if its about a shark who kills in the water, why not just stay out of the water?
I think it was more a government thing.  The Mayor tried to convince the public that the waters were safe.
Oh, I see! Thats fascinating! A little mystery and greed type story-line playing along side of the horrors of the ocean. That make it much more interesting to me.
Yeah, I agree.  I wonder if it's on Netflix.
Im sure it is - they seem to have everything these days. I wonder what it would have been like to see it on a big screen!
It was great talking to you!  I think this is the end of the 12 turns!
Oh, you too. Thank you for the info! :)
You're welcome!
I will certainly look into Jaws! Sounds great.
Definitely!

uid2response.feedback: The film sounded interesting. It was a horror movie with a very acclaimed director. The story sounded somewhat basic but has an underlying story of political misconduct and other interesting bits. It was Jaws, and I think they made it sound very interesting to watch.
